  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The validation evidence is drawn from a multi-site observational data collection programme in which construct failure loads and stiffness were recorded under standardised ASTM F1717 fixture geometry; the programme is described at length in the supporting study report and provides the primary basis for the output comparison. The narrative treats the observational programme as directly satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement because the fixture geometry and load application rate were standardised across sites, but the structured activity record reflects the actual data-collection design.",
