    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic isotropic material model and penalty-contact formulation are appropriate for the load regime; justification documented.",
      "rationale": "Pedicle screw and test block materials remain in the elastic regime for loads up to yield force. Linear elastic isotropic Ti-6Al-4V properties (E=114 GPa, nu=0.34) are well-established. Penalty contact with friction (mu=0.2) captures screw-block interface behaviour. Model form appropriate for the COU load regime."
