      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the regulatory submission claims for the non-cannulated design.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs correspond directly to the performance claims in the 510(k) submission: construct stiffness characterises load transfer, yield force characterises fatigue life proxy, and force at 40 mm characterises post-yield reserve. All QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision."
